<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('partials/head', { title: 'web-obsidian · your knowledge vault in the browser' }) %>
</head>
<body class="landing-page">
  <header class="landing-nav">
    <a class="landing-brand" href="/">web-obsidian</a>
    <nav class="landing-nav-actions">
      <select class="lang-select" data-lang-switch aria-label="Language" data-i18n-attr="aria-label:lang_switch">
        <option value="en">EN</option>
        <option value="de">DE</option>
      </select>
      <a class="btn-ghost" href="/docs" data-i18n="nav_docs">Docs</a>
      <a class="btn-ghost" href="/login" data-i18n="nav_signin">Sign in</a>
      <% if (typeof allowRegistration !== 'undefined' && allowRegistration) { %>
        <a class="btn-primary btn-inline" href="/register" data-i18n="nav_create">Create account</a>
      <% } %>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main class="landing-main">
    <section class="hero">
      <h1 data-i18n="hero_title">Your knowledge vault, in the browser.</h1>
      <p class="hero-lead" data-i18n="hero_lead">
        web-obsidian is an open-source, privacy-first knowledge vault you reach from any
        browser. Take notes, organize nested folders, sketch with Excalidraw and read PDFs &mdash;
        all online, with nothing to install. Everything is end-to-end encrypted in your browser,
        so only you can read your vault &mdash; not even the server can.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn-primary btn-inline" href="/login" data-i18n="hero_open">Open your vault</a>
        <% if (typeof allowRegistration !== 'undefined' && allowRegistration) { %>
          <a class="btn-ghost" href="/register" data-i18n="hero_create_free">Create a free account</a>
        <% } %>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="landing-section notice-section">
      <h2 data-i18n="why_title">Why web-obsidian — and what it is not</h2>
      <p class="section-lead" data-i18n="why_not">
        web-obsidian is an independent open-source project. It is not the original Obsidian
        (obsidian.md), not affiliated with it, and not a competitor. The name only describes the
        idea: an Obsidian-style markdown vault you open in any browser.
      </p>
      <p class="section-lead" data-i18n="why_reason">
        The original Obsidian keeps notes locally on each device and relies on a sync service to
        keep them aligned. In many companies you simply cannot install private sync clients or
        extra apps on enterprise laptops — so that setup is impossible. A browser is almost
        always available, so your vault stays reachable. Nothing to install, no local storage
        used on your phone or PC, and no encrypted backups for you to manage.
      </p>
      <p class="section-lead docs-quote" data-i18n="why_brain">
        It is intentionally simple — just what you need in daily work and private life. The human
        brain is made for having ideas, not for holding them. This is your second brain.
      </p>
      <p class="section-lead">
        <a class="text-link" href="/docs" data-i18n="why_learn_more">Read the documentation →</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="landing-section">
      <h2 data-i18n="diff_title">How it differs from obsidian.md</h2>
      <p class="section-lead" data-i18n="diff_lead">
        The original Obsidian is a great desktop app that keeps your notes offline on each device
        and relies on a sync service to keep them in step. web-obsidian flips that
        around: your vault lives online, end-to-end encrypted, and you simply log in with 2FA.
      </p>
      <div class="compare-grid">
        <div class="compare-card">
          <h3 data-i18n="card_nosync_h">Nothing to sync</h3>
          <p data-i18n="card_nosync_p">
            There is no sync to set up or pay for. Your notes are always in one place &mdash;
            log in from a laptop, PC or phone and pick up exactly where you left off.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="compare-card">
          <h3 data-i18n="card_browser_h">Browser-native</h3>
          <p data-i18n="card_browser_p">
            Built for the cloud and the browser instead of an offline desktop install. Open a
            tab on any device and your full vault is there.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="compare-card">
          <h3 data-i18n="card_secure_h">Account-based &amp; secure</h3>
          <p data-i18n="card_secure_p">
            Access is protected by your account with required two-factor authentication (2FA).
            Privacy comes first &mdash; no tracking, no analytics.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="compare-card">
          <h3 data-i18n="card_enc_h">Zero-knowledge encryption</h3>
          <p data-i18n="card_enc_p">
            Your notes, drawings and files are encrypted in your browser with AES-256-GCM. The
            server only ever receives ciphertext, so nobody &mdash; not even us &mdash; can read
            your vault.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="compare-card">
          <h3 data-i18n="card_oss_h">Open source</h3>
          <p data-i18n="card_oss_p">
            The full source code is public. Use the hosted version or self-host it yourself
            from the published container image.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="landing-section">
      <h2 data-i18n="features_title">Features</h2>
      <p class="section-lead" data-i18n="features_lead">
        All the everyday building blocks you need available
        online.
      </p>
      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li><i class="bi bi-file-earmark-text"></i> <span data-i18n="feat_notes">Markdown notes with live preview</span></li>
        <li><i class="bi bi-folder2-open"></i> <span data-i18n="feat_folders">Nested folders to organize your vault</span></li>
        <li><i class="bi bi-diagram-3"></i> <span data-i18n="feat_links">Wiki-style links between notes</span></li>
        <li><i class="bi bi-link-45deg"></i> <span data-i18n="feat_weblinks">Web link manager &mdash; save &amp; reopen trusted links</span></li>
        <li><i class="bi bi-pencil"></i> <span data-i18n="feat_excalidraw">Excalidraw drawing integration</span></li>
        <li><i class="bi bi-file-earmark-pdf"></i> <span data-i18n="feat_pdf">Built-in PDF viewer</span></li>
        <li><i class="bi bi-paperclip"></i> <span data-i18n="feat_attach">Attachments &amp; file uploads</span></li>
        <li><i class="bi bi-search"></i> <span data-i18n="feat_search">Full-text search that runs in your browser</span></li>
        <li><i class="bi bi-box-arrow-down"></i> <span data-i18n="feat_export">Export your whole vault as a decrypted zip</span></li>
        <li><i class="bi bi-shield-lock"></i> <span data-i18n="feat_2fa">Two-factor authentication (2FA)</span></li>
        <li><i class="bi bi-lock"></i> <span data-i18n="feat_enc">Zero-knowledge end-to-end encryption</span></li>
        <li><i class="bi bi-key"></i> <span data-i18n="feat_recovery">Recovery key to restore access if you forget your password</span></li>
        <li><i class="bi bi-moon-stars"></i> <span data-i18n="feat_themes">Light &amp; dark themes</span></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="landing-section">
      <h2 data-i18n="e2e_title">Zero-knowledge by design</h2>
      <p class="section-lead" data-i18n="e2e_lead">
        Your vault is encrypted and decrypted entirely in your browser. Your password never
        leaves your device, and the server only ever stores ciphertext it cannot read.
      </p>
      <div class="compare-grid">
        <div class="compare-card">
          <h3 data-i18n="e2e_point_keys_h">Only you hold the keys</h3>
          <p data-i18n="e2e_point_keys_p">
            Your encryption key is derived from your password in your browser and is never sent
            to the server. We physically cannot read your notes, drawings or files.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="compare-card">
          <h3 data-i18n="e2e_point_recovery_h">Keep your recovery key safe</h3>
          <p data-i18n="e2e_point_recovery_p">
            When you sign up you receive a one-time recovery key. It is the only way back in if
            you ever forget your password. Store it somewhere safe.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="compare-card">
          <h3 data-i18n="e2e_point_lost_h">Lost password, lost data</h3>
          <p data-i18n="e2e_point_lost_p">
            Because nobody but you can decrypt your vault, we cannot reset your password for you.
            If you lose both your password and your recovery key, the data is gone for good.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="landing-section pricing-section" id="pricing">
      <h2 data-i18n="pricing_title">Simple, encrypted storage</h2>
      <p class="section-lead" data-i18n="pricing_lead">
        Start free with 1 GB. Upgrade when you need more room — every plan is encrypted at rest.
      </p>
      <div class="pricing-grid">
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <h3 data-i18n="pricing_free_name">Free</h3>
          <p class="pricing-amount" data-i18n="pricing_free_amount">1 GB</p>
          <p class="pricing-desc" data-i18n="pricing_free_desc">Encrypted storage. No payment required.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pricing-card featured">
          <h3 data-i18n="pricing_5gb_name">5 GB</h3>
          <p class="pricing-amount"><%= (typeof pricing !== 'undefined' && pricing.price5gb) ? pricing.price5gb : '—' %><span class="pricing-period" data-i18n="pricing_per_year"> / year</span></p>
          <p class="pricing-desc" data-i18n="pricing_enc_desc">Encrypted storage for your growing vault.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <h3 data-i18n="pricing_20gb_name">20 GB</h3>
          <p class="pricing-amount"><%= (typeof pricing !== 'undefined' && pricing.price20gb) ? pricing.price20gb : '—' %><span class="pricing-period" data-i18n="pricing_per_year"> / year</span></p>
          <p class="pricing-desc" data-i18n="pricing_enc_desc">Encrypted storage for your growing vault.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="section-lead pricing-contact">
        <span data-i18n="pricing_more">Need more storage?</span>
        <% if (typeof pricing !== 'undefined' && pricing.contactEmail) { %>
          <a class="text-link" href="mailto:<%= pricing.contactEmail %>"><%= pricing.contactEmail %></a>
        <% } else { %>
          <span data-i18n="pricing_contact_us">Contact us.</span>
        <% } %>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="landing-cta">
      <h2 data-i18n="cta_title">Ready to start?</h2>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn-primary btn-inline" href="/login" data-i18n="nav_signin">Sign in</a>
        <% if (typeof allowRegistration !== 'undefined' && allowRegistration) { %>
          <a class="btn-ghost" href="/register" data-i18n="nav_create">Create account</a>
        <% } %>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
